What is the following structure? <image 1>

A. Doxorubicin
B. Dactinomycin
C. Mitoxantrone
D. Bleomycin

The structure in the image shows a tricyclic system with two cyclic peptides attached to it. The tricyclic system has a quinone ring and an amino group, which are characteristic features of dactinomycin.

Dactinomycin is an antitumor antibiotic that contains a tricyclic system with two cyclic peptides attached. The cyclic peptides are composed of N-methyl-L-valine (N-Me-L-Val), L-proline (L-Pro), and D-valine (D-Val).

Therefore, the correct answer is:

B. Dactinomycin
